                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#106r #106v" facs="107 108">fols. 106r, 106v</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> with caption <q>“Saint Filatawos”</q> (possibly a martyr) spearing an ox</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> with a list of names written upside down</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#3v" facs="005">Fol. 3v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref> with captions <q>“King and Prophet David,”</q> and <q>“Harp.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#16r" facs="017">Fol. 16r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> attended by the angels <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#30r" facs="031">Fol. 30r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> with captions <q>“Saint George,” and “dragon.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#49r" facs="050">Fol. 49r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref> raising Adam and Eve. with captions <q>“Our Mother, Eve,”</q> <q>“How Our Lord Jesus Christ rose from the Dead on the Third Day,”</q> and <q>“With our Father, Adam.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#91r" facs="092">Fol. 91r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1030Trinity">The Trinity</ref> with captions <q>“Holy Trinity,”</q> and <q>“with four creatures.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#109r" facs="110">Fol. 109r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1067LastSupper">The Last Supper</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#130r" facs="131">Fol. 130r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref> with caption right: <q>“Jesus Christ”</q> The patron reclines to the left: Caption: <q>“Yätnäbärǝḫ”</q> (a name which means, “Where have you been?”)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#130v" facs="132">Fol. 130v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1033Ascension">Ascension of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“The Ascension of Our Lord, Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#131r" facs="132">Fol. 131r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> Alexander, riding an Eagle-horse toward the angel who guards Paradise</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#131v" facs="133">Fol. 131v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1101GodFatherOrb"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1101GodFatherOrb</span></ref> God the Father holding orb of authority in his left hand and his right hand raised in blessing. with caption <q>“How Father and Son. . .”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d13">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #66v #67r" facs="002 068 068">folss. 1r, 66v, 67r, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#7v #14r #21r #30v #36v #40v #47v #55v #66v #76r #84v #87r #92v #98r #109v #115r #130r" facs="009 015 022 032 038 042 049 057 068 077 086 088 094 099 111 116 131">7v, 14r, 21r, 30v, 36v, 40v, 47v, 55v, 66v, 76r, 84v, 87r, 92v, 98r, 109v, 115r, 130r</locus> (line of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#52r" facs="053">Fol. 52r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    a small cross, written in a later hand, in the margin, in pencil, marks the midpoint of the <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#130r" facs="131">Fol. 130r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Original owner’s name has been erased and replaced by the name, Mäkfältä Maryam. Another name: [illegible] Wälättä Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#3 #15 #29 #48 #90 #108" facs="004 016 030 049 091 109">Fols. 3, 15, 29, 48, 90, 108</locus>
                    <desc>
                    purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge to indicate location of illumination as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#2v #9r #50v #60r #61r" facs="004 010 052 061 062">Fols. 2v, 9r, 50v, 60r, 61r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#42r #43r #78v #101r #101v" facs="043 044 080 102 103">Fols. 42r, 43r, 78v, 101r, 101v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#58v #61v #72r #121r" facs="060 063 073 122">Fols. 58v, 61v, 72r, 121r</locus>
                    <desc>erasure markings are visible</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#12r #55v #65r #103v #104r" facs="013 057 066 105 105">Fols. 12r, 55v, 65r, 103v, 104r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#35v #37r #41v" facs="037 038 043">Fols. 35v, 37r, 41v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
